<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFB5F720FE876AEEFD58E1B3" blockId="1.[277,665,1475,1496]" box="[277,665,1475,1496]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">
<heading id="D0E78180FFB5F720FE876AEEFD58E1B3" box="[277,665,1475,1496]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" reason="2">
HISTORY OF 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FE3B6AEEFDD7E1BC" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[425,534,1475,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FE3B6AEEFDD7E1BC" box="[425,534,1475,1496]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">GRAMMIA</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
TAXONOMY
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30A6567FFB5F723FF366AC7FD90E26B" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="509" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFB5F720FF366AC7FADEE038" blockId="1.[164,779,1514,1903]" lastBlockId="1.[826,1441,871,1903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">
The first 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FE836AC7FE18E26B" box="[273,473,1514,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FE836AC7FEBEE194" box="[273,383,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
to be named was 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FD226AC7FF1CE275" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Bombycidae" genus="Bombyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgo">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FD226AC7FF1CE275" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Bombyx virgo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by Carolus 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FE156925FD88E275" author="Linnaeus C" box="[391,585,1544,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" pagination="10" refId="ref63075" refString="Linnaeus C. 1758. [Lepidoptera]. In: Systema Naturae, etc. Edition 10. Holmiae." type="book chapter" year="1758">Linnaeus (1758)</bibRefCitation>
in his seminal 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FF36690AFEB5E257" box="[164,372,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Systema Naturae</emphasis>
, and the majority of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FD0E690AFCCBE257" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[668,778,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FD0E690AFCCBE257" box="[668,778,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
names were proposed by A. R. Grote, B. Neumögen, H. Strecker, and R. H. Stretch, all of whom figure prominently in the nomenclature of North American moths. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FE95698FFD99E2DC" author="Neumogen B &amp; Dyar HG" box="[263,600,1697,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" pagination="3 - 15" refId="ref63797" refString="Neumogen B, Dyar HG. 1894. A preliminary revision of the Bombyces of North America North of Mexico. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 2: 3 - 15." type="journal article" year="1894">Neumögen &amp; Dyar (1894)</bibRefCitation>
included the 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FF3669EDFED3E2BE" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[164,274,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FF3669EDFED3E2BE" box="[164,274,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group of genera (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FD9D69EDFDBCE2BE" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[527,637,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FD9D69EDFDBCE2BE" box="[527,637,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FD0E69EDFF33E29F" authority="Harris" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FD0E69EDFCCBE2BE" box="[668,778,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis</emphasis>
Harris
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FE9469F2FDD1E29F" authority="M. E. Smith" authorityName="M. E. Smith" box="[262,528,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FE9469F2FEB3E29F" box="[262,370,1759,1780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Notarctia</emphasis>
M.E. Smith
</taxonomicName>
) in their treatment of North American moths, uniting all these in one genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FEA36831FDC1E359" authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1820" box="[305,512,1820,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Euprepia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FEA36831FE5BE35A" box="[305,410,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Euprepia</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, with five constituent species-groups. These groups were based on wing pattern similarities, and largely did not correspond to subsequent groupings, with the exception of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FCA86CABFC69E7F0" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[826,936,902,923]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FCA86CABFC69E7F0" box="[826,936,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, which was subsequently recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FCCC6C88FC0DE7D1" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[862,972,933,954]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FCCC6C88FC0DE7D1" box="[862,972,933,954]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="C6920357FFB5F720FC4D6C89FBF3E7D1" box="[991,1074,932,954]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="1.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Taxonomic history of the genus Grammia" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Table 1</tableCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FBDF6C88FACDE7D1" author="Hampson G" box="[1101,1292,932,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref62500" refString="Hampson G. 1901. Catalogue of the Arctiadae (Arctianae) and Agaristidae in the collection of the British Museum (Natural History). In: Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the collection of the British Museum (Natural History). London." type="book" year="1901">Hampson (1901)</bibRefCitation>
included all three currently recognized genera under 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FABE6CEEFA5BE7B3" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[1324,1434,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FABE6CEEFA5BE7B3" box="[1324,1434,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also including the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FB146CCCFC4CE07D" authority="(de Villers)" baseAuthorityName="de Villers" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Atlantarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FB146CCCFAAFE79C" box="[1158,1390,993,1015]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Atlantarctia tigrina</emphasis>
(de Villers)
</taxonomicName>
[as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FC4B6B2DFAE1E07D" authority="(Esper)" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1785" box="[985,1312,1024,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FC4B6B2DFB74E07E" box="[985,1205,1024,1045]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis fasciata</emphasis>
(Esper)
</taxonomicName>
, a junior synonym]. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FC256B32FB61E05E" author="McDunnough J" box="[951,1184,1055,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" pagination="275" refId="ref63293" refString="McDunnough J. 1938. Checklist of Lepidoptera of Canada and the United States of America. Part 1. Macrolepidoptera. Memoirs of the Southern California Academy of Sciences 1: 275." type="journal article" year="1938">McDunnough (1938)</bibRefCitation>
maintained the genus name usage of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FC7F6B13FB6AE038" author="Hampson G" box="[1005,1195,1085,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref62500" refString="Hampson G. 1901. Catalogue of the Arctiadae (Arctianae) and Agaristidae in the collection of the British Museum (Natural History). In: Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the collection of the British Museum (Natural History). London." type="book" year="1901">Hampson (1901)</bibRefCitation>
(
<tableCitation id="C6920357FFB5F720FB2E6B10FACEE038" box="[1212,1295,1085,1107]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="1.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Taxonomic history of the genus Grammia" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFB5F723FCC16B71FDDDE51E" blockId="1.[826,1441,871,1903]" lastBlockId="2.[144,759,198,1536]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="509" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">
The species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FB8B6B71FB46E01A" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[1049,1159,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FB8B6B71FB46E01A" box="[1049,1159,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were first revised by Marion Smith in an unpublished doctoral thesis (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FCD06BB4FC29E0C4" author="Smith ME" box="[834,1000,1177,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith, 1938a</bibRefCitation>
), which also included species now placed in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FBAC6B95FB6DE0A6" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[1086,1196,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FBAC6B95FB6DE0A6" box="[1086,1196,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FB7D6B95FA9AE0A6" box="[1263,1371,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FB7D6B95FA9AE0A6" box="[1263,1371,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Notarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This work was unfortunately published only as a 12-page abstract (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FC386BD8FB8BE160" author="Smith ME" box="[938,1098,1269,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref64436" refString="Smith ME. 1938 b. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). An Abstract of a thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith, 1938b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FBF26BD8FAC7E160" author="Smith ME" box="[1120,1286,1269,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith (1938a)</bibRefCitation>
included the modern concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FB9C6A39FBBDE142" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[1038,1148,1300,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FB9C6A39FBBDE142" box="[1038,1148,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FB186A39FB37E142" box="[1162,1270,1300,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FB186A39FB37E142" box="[1162,1270,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Notarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FAA76A3EFA60E143" authorityName="M. E. Smith" authorityYear="1938" box="[1333,1441,1299,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Holarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FAA76A3EFA60E143" box="[1333,1441,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Holarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(revised status, see below) as subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FABC6A1FFC5AE10C" authority="Packard" authorityName="Packard" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Callarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FABC6A1FFA60E12C" box="[1326,1441,1330,1351]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Callarctia</emphasis>
Packard
</taxonomicName>
, and treated 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FBAF6A7CFB6AE10D" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[1085,1195,1361,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FBAF6A7CFB6AE10D" box="[1085,1195,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
separately (
<tableCitation id="C6920357FFB5F720FAAC6A7CFA50E10C" box="[1342,1425,1361,1383]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="1.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Taxonomic history of the genus Grammia" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Table 1</tableCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FCA86A42FC24E1EE" author="Smith ME" box="[826,997,1391,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith (1938a)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 22 species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FABE6A5DFA5BE1EE" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[1324,1434,1392,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FABE6A5DFA5BE1EE" box="[1324,1434,1392,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, compared to the 24 species listed by McDunnough shortly prior to her revision in his ‘Check List of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FCA86AE6FC05E18A" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[826,964,1483,1505]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F307767CFFB5F720FB976AE6FB9CE18A" box="[1029,1117,1483,1505]" name="Canada" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Canada</collectingCountry>
and the United States’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FCD06AC7FBE7E26B" author="McDunnough J" box="[834,1062,1514,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" pagination="275" refId="ref63293" refString="McDunnough J. 1938. Checklist of Lepidoptera of Canada and the United States of America. Part 1. Macrolepidoptera. Memoirs of the Southern California Academy of Sciences 1: 275." type="journal article" year="1938">McDunnough, 1938</bibRefCitation>
). Five taxa treated as species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FCA86925FBECE275" author="McDunnough J" box="[826,1069,1544,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" pagination="275" refId="ref63293" refString="McDunnough J. 1938. Checklist of Lepidoptera of Canada and the United States of America. Part 1. Macrolepidoptera. Memoirs of the Southern California Academy of Sciences 1: 275." type="journal article" year="1938">McDunnough (1938)</bibRefCitation>
were informally synonymized by Smith (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FC52690AFAE1E256" authority="Strecker" authorityName="Strecker" box="[960,1312,1575,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadranotata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FC52690AFB71E257" box="[960,1200,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Arctia quadranotata</emphasis>
Strecker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FAA1690AFBF3E230" authority="McDunnough" authorityName="McDunnough" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibsoni">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FAA1690AFC4DE231" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis gibsoni</emphasis>
McDunnough
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FBAD696BFA8CE230" authority="Stretch" authorityName="Stretch" box="[1087,1357,1605,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FBAD696BFB2EE231" box="[1087,1263,1605,1627]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Arctia elongata</emphasis>
Stretch
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FAC9696BFBD5E211" authority="Stretch" authorityName="Stretch" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FAC9696BFC77E212" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Arctia intermedia</emphasis>
Stretch
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FBC16949FAA3E211" authority="Strecker" authorityName="Strecker" box="[1107,1378,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oithona">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FBC16949FB36E212" box="[1107,1271,1636,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Arctia oithona</emphasis>
Strecker
</taxonomicName>
), and three taxa were raised to species status (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FA8669AEFCA9E2DD" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quenselii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FA8669AEFCA9E2DD" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Arctia quenselii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ab. 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FC0E698CFBB2E2DC" authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[924,1139,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FC0E698CFBD6E2DD" box="[924,1047,1697,1718]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">complicata</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FBED698CFA5DE2DC" authority="Stretch" authorityName="Stretch" box="[1151,1436,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FBED698CFAFFE2DD" box="[1151,1342,1697,1718]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Arctia edwardsii</emphasis>
Stretch
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FCE469EDFC45E29F" authority="Barnes &amp; McDunnough" authorityName="Barnes &amp; McDunnough" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ornata" subSpecies="hewletti">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FCE469EDFB6DE2BE" box="[886,1196,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Apantesis ornata hewletti</emphasis>
Barnes &amp; McDunnough
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB5F720FC3369F3FB8CE29F" author="Smith ME" box="[929,1101,1758,1780]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith (1938a)</bibRefCitation>
did not describe any new species, but, more importantly, provided the genusgroup names 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FC456831FB11E359" authority="M. E. Smith" authorityName="M. E. Smith" authorityYear="1938" box="[983,1232,1820,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Holarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FC456831FB82E35A" box="[983,1091,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Holarctia</emphasis>
M.E. Smith
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FA996831FAB6E35A" box="[1291,1399,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FA996831FAB6E35A" box="[1291,1399,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Notarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To this end, Smith’s most significant contribution to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB5F720FCA86874FC69E305" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[826,936,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB5F720FCA86874FC69E305" box="[826,936,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxonomy was in defining groups based on structural characters of the larvae, pupae, and adult genitalia, her work reflected in the modern concepts of the two 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FEBF6E2EFE5AE573" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[301,411,259,280]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FEBF6E2EFE5AE573" box="[301,411,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgenera (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FDD26E29FD79E572" box="[576,696,260,281]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mimarctia">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FDD26E29FD79E572" box="[576,696,260,281]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Mimarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF026E0FFF3FE55C" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[144,254,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF026E0FFF3FE55C" box="[144,254,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FE8B6E0FFE46E55C" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[281,391,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FE8B6E0FFE46E55C" box="[281,391,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FE586E0FFDF7E55C" box="[458,566,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FE586E0FFDF7E55C" box="[458,566,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Notarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although these genera/subgenera were not formally recognized for nearly another 50 years (
<tableCitation id="C6920357FFB6F723FE2B6E72FDCDE51E" box="[441,524,351,373]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="1.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Taxonomic history of the genus Grammia" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFB6F723FF3A6E50FDF3E6AE" blockId="2.[144,759,198,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
Shortly after Smith’s work, Eugene Munroe summarized 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF686EB1FEA9E5DA" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[250,360,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF686EB1FEA9E5DA" box="[250,360,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FEEC6EB1FE2DE5DA" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[382,492,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FEEC6EB1FE2DE5DA" box="[382,492,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FDA86EB0FD67E5D9" box="[570,678,413,434]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FDA86EB0FD67E5D9" box="[570,678,413,434]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Notarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in an unpublished MSc thesis, wherein he maintained the generic and subgeneric usage proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FF026ED5FEEEE666" author="Smith ME" box="[144,303,504,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith (1938a</bibRefCitation>
, b), and further grouped the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF026D3AFF3FE647" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[144,254,535,556]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF026D3AFF3FE647" box="[144,254,535,556]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FEAF6D3BFE71E640" authorityName="Packard" authorityYear="1864" box="[317,432,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Callarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FEAF6D3BFE71E640" box="[317,432,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Callarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FDD26D3BFD72E640" authorityName="Packard" authorityYear="1864" box="[576,691,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Callarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FDD26D3BFD72E640" box="[576,691,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Callarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) into three species groups based on general wing pattern similarities (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FEB76D79FE0AE601" author="Munroe E" box="[293,459,596,618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" refId="ref63559" refString="Munroe E. 1941. A study of the genera Callarctia and Apantesis (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Unpublished M. Sc. thesis, Macdonald College, Ste. Anne de Bellevue, Quebec." type="book" year="1941">Munroe, 1941</bibRefCitation>
). No new species or synonymies were proposed by Munroe, although he recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF6B6DBCFDA0E6CC" authority="Strecker" authorityName="Strecker" box="[249,609,657,679]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadranotata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF6B6DBCFE2CE6CD" box="[249,493,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Arctia quadranotata</emphasis>
Strecker
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FD226DBCFE8FE6AE" authority="Stretch" authorityName="Stretch" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FD226DBCFF30E6AF" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Arctia elongata</emphasis>
Stretch
</taxonomicName>
as distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFB6F723FF3A6DE3FDB8E038" blockId="2.[144,759,198,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
The generic and subgeneric definitions proposed by Smith were not adopted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FD8E6DC0FD09E768" author="Forbes WTM" box="[540,712,749,771]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" refId="ref61833" refString="Forbes WTM. 1960. The Lepidoptera of New York and neighboring states. Part IV. Agaristidae through Nymphalidae, including butterflies. Ithaca, NY: Cornell University Agricultural Experiment Station Memoir no. 371." type="book" year="1960">Forbes (1960)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FF026C26FEB8E74A" author="Franclemont JG" box="[144,377,779,801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="114 - 119" refId="ref61913" refString="Franclemont JG. 1983. Arctiidae. In: Hodges RW, ed. Check list of the Lepidoptera of North America north of Mexico. London: E. W. Classey Ltd. and the Wedge Entomological Research Foundation, 114 - 119." type="book chapter" year="1983">Franclemont (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, both of whom included under 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF026C07FF3FE754" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[144,254,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF026C07FF3FE754" box="[144,254,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
all species under the current concepts of 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF026C64FE40E735" box="[144,385,841,862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF026C64FEC0E735" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[144,257,841,862]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Grammia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FE876C64FE40E735" box="[277,385,841,862]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Notarctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Notarctia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FE406C64FD81E735" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1841" box="[466,576,841,862]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apantesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FE406C64FD81E735" box="[466,576,841,862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Apantesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="C6920357FFB6F723FDCA6C65FD6AE734" box="[600,683,840,863]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="1.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Taxonomic history of the genus Grammia" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Table 1</tableCitation>
). The current generic arrangement follows that proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FF026CABFE8DE7F0" author="Ferguson DC" box="[144,332,901,923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="181 - 275" refId="ref61641" refString="Ferguson DC. 1985. Contributions toward reclassification of the world genera of the tribe Arctiini. Part 1 - Introduction and a revision of the Neoarctia-Grammia group (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae; Arctiinae). Entomography 3: 181 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Ferguson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
, who was the first to apply the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FF026C88FF3FE7D1" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[144,254,933,954]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF026C88FF3FE7D1" box="[144,254,933,954]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to North American taxa, following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FD246C88FED7E7B2" author="Inoue H &amp; Sugi S &amp; Kuroko H &amp; Moriuti S &amp; Kawabe A" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" refId="ref62725" refString="Inoue H, Sugi S, Kuroko H, Moriuti S, Kawabe A. 1982. Moths of Japan. Volume 1 (text). Tokyo: Kodansha." type="book" year="1982">
Inoue 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FF026CEEFF09E7B3" box="[144,200,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">et al.</emphasis>
(1982)
</bibRefCitation>
who applied 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FE3D6CEEFDDCE7B3" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[431,541,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FE3D6CEEFDDCE7B3" box="[431,541,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FDD06CEEFEEDE79C" authority="(Paykull)" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1793" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quenseli">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FDD06CEEFF77E79D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia quenseli</emphasis>
(Paykull)
</taxonomicName>
. New 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FEE56CCFFD81E79C" box="[375,576,993,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FEE56CCFFE24E79C" box="[375,485,994,1015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
were described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FF206B2DFEACE07D" author="Ferguson DC" box="[178,365,1024,1046]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="181 - 275" refId="ref61641" refString="Ferguson DC. 1985. Contributions toward reclassification of the world genera of the tribe Arctiini. Part 1 - Introduction and a revision of the Neoarctia-Grammia group (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae; Arctiinae). Entomography 3: 181 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Ferguson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FEEB6B2DFD01E07D" author="Dubatolov VV &amp; Schmidt BC" box="[377,704,1024,1046]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="53 - 54" refId="ref61375" refString="Dubatolov VV, Schmidt BC. 2005. A new species of the genus Grammia Rambur, 1866 (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae) from Northeastern Transbaikalia. Euroasian Entomological Journal 4: 53 - 54." type="journal article" year="2005">Dubatolov &amp; Schmidt (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FF026B32FE1EE05E" author="Ferguson DC &amp; Schmidt BC" box="[144,479,1055,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="39 - 49" refId="ref61798" refString="Ferguson DC, Schmidt BC. 2007. Taxonomic review of the Grammia nevadensis species group (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae) with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa 1405: 39 - 49." type="journal article" year="2007">Ferguson &amp; Schmidt (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, the latter providing a review of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FEA06B13FDE7E039" baseAuthorityName="Grote &amp; Robinson" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[306,550,1085,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FEA06B13FDE7E039" box="[306,550,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFB6F723FF3A6B71FD90E26B" blockId="2.[144,759,198,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
The paucity of genitalic variation amongst species and even species-groups of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFB6F723FE5D6B56FDFCE0FB" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[463,573,1147,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFB6F723FE5D6B56FDFCE0FB" box="[463,573,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been a significant impediment to the taxonomy of this genus, compounded by the apparent rarity of many western species. The discovery of additional morphological characters (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FE856BD8FD8DE161" author="Ferguson DC &amp; Schmidt BC" box="[279,588,1269,1291]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="39 - 49" refId="ref61798" refString="Ferguson DC, Schmidt BC. 2007. Taxonomic review of the Grammia nevadensis species group (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae) with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa 1405: 39 - 49." type="journal article" year="2007">Ferguson &amp; Schmidt, 2007</bibRefCitation>
; this revision), coupled with the availability of a greater number of museum specimens, has however provided a muchimproved taxonomic resolution of this group. As discussed below, the taxonomic utility of mitochondrial DNA data (cytochrome oxidase I gene) has proven to be minimal, and in fact points to a significant decoupling of genomic integrity from mitochondrial DNA genealogy (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFFB6F723FE806AC7FD87E26B" author="Schmidt BC &amp; Sperling FAH" box="[274,582,1514,1536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="613 - 634" refId="ref64151" refString="Schmidt BC, Sperling FAH. 2008. Widespread decoupling of mtDNA variation and species integrity in Grammia tiger moths (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae). Systematic Entomology 33: 613 - 634." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmidt &amp; Sperling, 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
